      <title>1843 March 20, Rock Cave, K[entuck]y [to] Emaline Hamilton, Nashville, Tenn[essee]</title>
   </titleInfo>
   <abstract>This is a letter to Emaline Hamilton from her sister Mary. It is dated March 20, 1843. Mary starts by apologizing to Emaline for not writing as often as she should. Mary writes about going to parties and to church since she has been in Rock Cave. She mentions how some people were scared of the Great Comet of 1843. Some believed it heralded the Second Coming. She sends her love to many family members.</abstract>
